			<h1>Design System Multi-Point Inspection Kit</h1>
			<p><strong>Pop the hood. Roll up your sleeves. Figure out what&rsquo;s causing that check engine light.</strong></p>
			<p>This kit turns the <a href="/checklist/">multi-point inspection checklist</a> into a real, runnable inspection you can point at <em>your</em> design system. An AI agent walks your system through the same 10 stations, gathers evidence, and hands back a red/yellow/green inspection report plus a prioritized work order.</p>
			<p>It&rsquo;s <strong>tool-agnostic</strong> and plain markdown&mdash;no required vendor, plugin, or framework. If your agent can reach your design file, repo, or docs, findings come back <code>[verified]</code>; if not, every station falls back gracefully to exports, screenshots, or a plain interview.</p>

			<p>The kit lives on GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/Brad-Frost-Web/ai-design-systems-inspection-kit">Brad-Frost-Web/ai-design-systems-inspection-kit</a> (free, MIT licensed).</p>

			<h2>Quick start (Claude Code)</h2>
			<ol>
				<li><strong>Install it.</strong> Clone into your personal skills folder&mdash;the folder name <code>ds-inspection</code> becomes the command:
					<br><code>git clone https://github.com/Brad-Frost-Web/ai-design-systems-inspection-kit.git ~/.claude/skills/ds-inspection</code>
					<br>Then restart Claude Code and open it inside the design system you want to inspect. (See the <a href="https://github.com/Brad-Frost-Web/ai-design-systems-inspection-kit#quick-start">README</a> for Cursor, Cowork, and plain-chat options.)</li>
				<li><strong>Check in your vehicle.</strong> Run <code>/ds-inspection</code> (or say <em>&ldquo;Run the design system multi-point inspection&mdash;start with intake&rdquo;</em>) and answer the garage-intake questions about your system&rsquo;s assets and access.</li>
				<li><strong>Run the stations.</strong> All ten in order, one at a time (&ldquo;run station 3&rdquo;), or re-inspect later to see what changed.</li>
			</ol>

